    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A pale yellow pigment used alone or mixed with other pigments, such as Prussian blue, barium yellow, and zinc yellow. It is used in oil paints, anticorrosive coatings, and pyrotechnics. It is not used often in watercolors due to its high opacity.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047822/MFA Conservation and Art Material Encyclopedia Online: CAMEO (2005-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種蒼黃色顏料，可單獨使用或與其它顏料混用，如普魯士藍、鋇黃和鋅黃。用於油畫、防腐塗層和煙火。因為高度不透明，不常用於水彩。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
